    title: "The ChatGPT browser is already dead",
    summary: "OpenAI is already shutting down ChatGPT Atlas, its browser that could do tasks for you on your behalf, less than a year after launching it. Atlas was announced in October, but as part of its wave of news about ChatGPT Work today, the company confirmed that it will be \"sunsetting\" Atlas and is targeting an [&#8230;]",
    body: "OpenAI is already shutting down ChatGPT Atlas, its browser that could do tasks for you on your behalf, less than a year after launching it. Atlas was announced in October , but as part of its wave of news about ChatGPT Work today , the company confirmed that it will be \"sunsetting\" Atlas and is targeting an August 9th date for deprecation. The shutdown follows OpenAI's push to reduce \"side quests\" and catch up with Anthropic on productivity features .\n\nAs part of that push, in March, The Wall Street Journal reported that OpenAI planned to combine the ChatGPT app, Codex, and Atlas into a desktop \"superapp\" - ChatGPT Work appears to be the result …",
